A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to motor vehicles and
2 traffic, so as to require the placement of a special identifying sticker on the windshields of
3 alternative fueled vehicles; to provide for the design and distribution of such stickers by the
4 Department of Revenue; to provide for the designation of a vehicle as an alternative fueled
5 vehicle on a motor vehicle registration application; to provide for a penalty; to provide for
6 exceptions; to provide for definitions; to provide for legislative findings and purpose; to
7 provide for related matters; to provide for an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and
8 for other purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 The General Assembly recognizes that the number of alternative fueled vehicles operating
12 on Georgia's highways continues to grow. Alternative fueled vehicles pose a unique
13 challenge to first responders, as different types of fuel can require specific safety procedures
14 in instances of an accident. Many alternative fueled vehicles are indistinguishable from
15 traditional gasoline powered vehicles. Requiring a special sticker to identify a vehicle as an
16 alternative vehicle and what type of fuel is used would assist first responders in quickly
