18 are necessary for the safety of first responders and the general public.
19 SECTION 2.
20 Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to motor vehicles and traffic, is
21 amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
22 "40-1-10.
23 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
24 (1) 'Alternative fueled vehicle' means a motor vehicle with a gross weight of 10,000
25 pounds or less fueled exclusively or partially by electricity, natural gas, hydrogen, or
26 propane.
27 (2) 'Alternative fueled vehicle sticker' means a sticker approved and provided by the
28 department designating a motor vehicle as an alternative fueled vehicle.
29 (3) 'Department' means the Department of Revenue.
30 (b) Upon approval of an application for the initial registration or renewal registration of
31 a motor vehicle that is an alternative fueled vehicle and payment of a fee of $3.00, the
32 department shall provide the owner with two alternative fueled vehicle stickers.
33 Alternative fueled vehicle stickers shall be of a design and material approved by the
34 department, provided that a separate design shall be used for each type of alternative fuel
35 and such stickers shall be of a size suitable for placement in the bottom corner of a
36 windshield with minimal obstruction of view for an operator. The department shall take
37 into consideration design standards set by the Society of Automotive Engineers in
38 designing alternative fueled vehicle stickers.
39 (c) Any person who owns an alternative fueled vehicle registered in this state shall affix
40 alternative fueled vehicle stickers to the bottom corner of the driver's side of the front and
41 rear windshield.
