42 (d)(1) Except as otherwise provided for in paragraph (2) of this subsection, a person who
43 fails to identify an alternative fueled vehicle as required in subsection (c) of this Code
44 section shall be guilty of a misdemeanor and, upon conviction thereof, shall be punished
45 by a fine not exceeding $100.00.
46 (2) The requirement set forth in subsection (c) of this Code section shall not apply:
47 (A) Within the first 45 days of any initial purchase of an alternative fueled vehicle; or
48 (B) Until an owner's registration period expires for an alternative fueled vehicle that
49 was registered in this state prior to January 1, 2026."
50 SECTION 3.
51 Said title is further amended in Code Section 40-2-26, relating to form and contents of
52 application for registration, heavy vehicle tax, and satisfactory proof of insurance coverage,
53 by revising paragraph (1) of subsection (b) as follows:
54 "(b)(1) Application shall be made by the owner of the vehicle upon a form prepared by
55 the commissioner for such purposes setting forth the name, place of residence, and
56 address of the applicant; a brief description of the vehicle to be registered, including its
57 name and model, the name of the manufacturer, the manufacturer's vehicle identification
58 number, and its shipping weight and carrying capacity, and whether it is an alternative
59 fueled vehicle as such term is defined in Code Section 40-1-10; from whom, where, and
60 when the vehicle was purchased; the total amount of all liens, if any, thereon, with the
61 name and address of the lienholder; and such other information as the commissioner may
62 require. Such application shall include a method for indicating whether the application
63 is for a digital license plate issued pursuant to Article 2B of this chapter."
64 SECTION 4.
65 This Act shall become effective on January 1, 2026.
